http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/Work-on-Azalapur-Edlur-road-to-cost-Rs.-2-crore/article13979922.ece

Textiles and Ports Minister Baburao Chinchansur laid the foundation stone for construction of a new road between Azalapur-Edlur villages in Yadgir taluk on Sunday.Addressing a gathering, Mr. Chinchansur, who is also district in-charge Minister, said that the State government was committed to implementing projects to develop rural areas with infrastructure, particularly drinking water and road, to ensure that the people are provided with basic amenities.The four-kilometre road will be constructed at a cost of Rs. 2.05 crore. He said that an industrial hub in Kadechur and Badiyal villages will be developed with all infrastructure, including roads, drinking water, drainage, at a cost of Rs. 100 crore. The Karnataka Industrial Area Development Board (KIADB) will release the money for the purpose, he added.